The government has extended the ongoing nationwide curfew by a further 60 days in efforts to try and cope with the third wave of the coronavirus in the country. both the 10 pm to 4 am curfew in the rest of the country and the 8 pm to 4 am curfew for the 5 counties within the designated zone will be up for review at the end of June even as county governors raise concern over the increasing rate of COVID-19 community infections. Timothy Otieno now reports.